{{nihongo|'''Dōmo arigatō'''|どうもありがとう|}} is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] expression that translates to "Thank you." Knowledge of the expression was popularized in the [[Western world]] at least in part by the song "[[Mr. Roboto]]" by [[Styx (band)|Styx]] which features the line "''Dōmo arigatō'', Mr. Roboto."

The line has been used as a pop culture reference a number of times, including in the film ''[[Austin Powers in Goldmember]]'', the song "The King of Bedside Manor" by the [[Barenaked Ladies]], cartoons ''[[Futurama]]'' and ''[[The Simpsons]]'', and the film ''[[Kill Bill: Volume II]]''.


